<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000176> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000002> .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000176> <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/identifier> "221-BFO" .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000176> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/lehrplan/ontology/> .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000176> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "continuant part of"@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000176> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "b continuant part of c =Def b and c are continuants & there is some time t such that b and c exist at t & b continuant part of c at t"@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000176> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Milk teeth continuant part of human; surgically removed tumour continuant part of organism"@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000176> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "continuant part of at some time"@en .
